                In <expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex>onorem</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>omus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ivinae</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> deae Neh<supplied reason="lost">alenniae</supplied> <lb n="2"/>aram Aest<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ivus</supplied> <lb n="3"/>Iuni Silvi ser<expan><ex>v</ex><abbr>us</abbr></expan> <lb n="4"/>Manchissa <lb n="5"/>ex voto <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>osuerunt</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibentes</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan>
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Über der Inschrift Reliefdarstellung der Göttin in einer aedicula. Z. 3: vom T nur noch das untere Ende der senkrechten Haste erhalten; deshalb z. B. auch Ergänzung Aesi[lus] möglich.</p>
            </div>
